Reasoning: The paper applies natural language processing methods to aid in literary analysis, which falls under the scope of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of pretrained contextualized representations and unsupervised clustering suggests the use of deep learning methods (cs.DL and cs.LG). The paper also involves comparing computational results to human judgments, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
